      "page_count": 1,
      "representative_comment_id": "FWS-HQ-LE-2026-0628-0015",
      "representative_posted_date": "2026-03-13T04:00:00Z",
      "representative_length": 457,
      "representative_excerpt": "While cephalopods are mollusks, they are not shellfish and must remain separate in class distinction for the sake of the shellfish industry. The current conditions on shellfish handling maintain quality above the world norm and adding the label shellfish to cephalopods does nothing to bolster this. Please protect the livelihoods of the countless families tha...",
      "submissions": {
        "FWS-HQ-LE-2026-0628-0015": {
          "organization": "Montauk Shellfish Company Inc.",
          "postedDate": "2026-03-13T04:00:00Z",
          "zip": "",
          "city": "",
          "stateProvinceRegion": "",
          "country": "",
          "attachmentCount": 0,
          "title": "Comment from Montauk Shellfish Company Inc.",
          "withdrawn": false
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "cluster_id": 5,
      "count": 1,
      "page_count": 1,
      "representative_comment_id": "FWS-HQ-LE-2026-0628-0011",
      "representative_posted_date": "2026-03-12T04:00:00Z",
      "representative_length": 413,
      "representative_excerpt": "The terminology may be scientifically confusing, but this sounds like an attempt to get out of regulating an industry that harvests octopuses, squid, and other cephalopods for human consumption. Is that in the best interest of managing wild stocks or protecting human health and safety? I oppose the change. If the taxonomy is confusing simply update the termi...",
      "submissions": {
        "FWS-HQ-LE-2026-0628-0011": {
          "organization": "",
          "postedDate": "2026-03-12T04:00:00Z",
          "zip": "",
          "city": "",
